4.
List all Departments that have no Employees currently assigned to them.
SELECT Departments.dept_name
FROM Departments
LEFT JOIN Employees
ON Departments.dept_id = Employees.dept_id
WHERE Employees.employee_id IS NULL;
________________________________________
5.
Show the Manager Name, the Department Name they manage, and the total number of direct reports they have.
SELECT Managers.employee_name AS Manager_Name,
Departments.dept_name,
COUNT(Employees.employee_id) AS Total_Reports
FROM Employees
INNER JOIN Employees AS Managers
ON Employees.manager_id = Managers.employee_id
INNER JOIN Departments
ON Managers.dept_id = Departments.dept_id
GROUP BY Managers.employee_name, Departments.dept_name;
